title: TEXAS TORNADOS - 4 CDS
description: This Texas supergroup&#039;s four frontmen had more than 200 years of experience playing live and recording between them. A left-field hybrid of norteno, Swamp Pop, rock &#039;n&#039; roll, blues, country and everything in between, Texas Tornadoes were fronted by Tejano star Flaco Jimenez, &#039;60s rock icon Doug Sahm, crooner Freddy Fender, and Sahm&#039;s cohort from the Sir Douglas Quintet, Augie Meyers. The Tornadoes hit the country charts with their debut album -- quite a feat considering how far removed from the Nashville norm the group&#039;s sound was. Though they never repeated that success on their subsequent records, the band retained a large and loyal worldwide following. They disbanded after the unexpected death of Doug Sahm in 1999.
